OL,3,CCourt told Joey Barton 'crossed the
OL,4,Cline between free speech and a crime'
OL,6,FHe said: "Some may even consider some
OL,7,Fof them humorous."Everyone is entitled
OL,8,Fto express views that are all of those
OL,9,Fthings. They are even entitled in a
OL,10,Fdemocratic, free society to express
OL,11,Fviews that are offensive, shocking or
OL,12,Fpersonally rude when considered
OL,13,Fagainst and applying the contemporary
OL,14,Fstandards of an open, just, multi-
OL,15,Fracial; equal and diverse society.
OL,17,F"What someone is not entitled to do is
OL,18,Fto post communications electronically
OL,19,Fthat are ` applying those standards `
OL,20,Fbeyond the pale of what is tolerable
OL,21,Fin society.
