OL,3,CCourt told Joey Barton 'crossed the
OL,4,Cline between free speech and a crime'
OL,6,F"We say that the defendant Mr Barton
OL,7,Fcrossed the line between free speech
OL,8,Fand a crime on 12 occasions.
OL,10,F"On 12 occasions between early January
OL,11,Fand mid-March last year, he engaged in
OL,12,Fa quite deliberate course of conduct
OL,13,Fin which he targeted three people, who
OL,14,Fare in different ways in the public
OL,15,Feye, and he subjected them through his
OL,16,Fposts to a slew of grossly offensive
OL,17,Felectronic communications with intent
OL,18,Fto cause distress or anxiety to the
OL,19,Frecipient or to any other person to
OL,20,Fwhom he intended its contents or
OL,21,Fnature to be communicated."
